(34, 1685046688, 1685034784, 1685046688, 'a', '01.a', '$P(B &#92;cup D)$', '1', 21, 1, '1', '1', '11', '1', '1', '\r\n $\r\n    P(B &#92;cup D)\r\n    =\r\n    P(B)+P(D)-P(B &#92;cap D)\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{7+9-3}{18}\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{13}{18}\r\n $.', '$&#92;frac{13}{18}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(35, 1685048444, 1685034821, 1685048444, 'b', '01.b', '$P(&#92;overline{A} &#92;cap &#92;overline{C})$', '1', 21, 1, '1', '1', '11', '1', '1', '$P(&#92;overline{A} &#92;cap &#92;overline{C})\r\n =\r\n P(B &#92;cap D)\r\n =\r\n &#92;frac{1}{6}\r\n $', '$&#92;frac{1}{6}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(37, 1685562225, 1685561848, 1685562225, 'a', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.02.a', 'Qual a probabilidade de que o menor n&uacute;mero de emblema seja 5?', '1', 22, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '6 n&uacute;meros (5,6,7,8,9 e 10) s&atilde;o $&#92;geq$ 5.\r\n Escolher $3$ de 6 pode ser feito em:\r\n&#92;[\r\n &#92;begin{pmatrix}6&#92;&#92;3&#92;end{pmatrix}\r\n =\r\n &#92;frac{6!}{3!(6-3)!}\r\n =\r\n &#92;frac{6!}{3!3!}\r\n =\r\n &#92;frac{6&#92;cdot 5 &#92;cdot 4}{6}\r\n = \r\n 20\r\n&#92;]\r\nOs que n&atilde;o cont&eacute;m 5 (somente 6,7,8,9,10):\r\n&#92;[    \r\n    &#92;begin{pmatrix}5&#92;&#92;3&#92;end{pmatrix}\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{5!}{3!(5-3)!}\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{5!}{3!2!}\r\n    =\r\n    10\r\n&#92;]\r\nContendo um 5 e os restantes maior: 20-10=10.\r\nProbabilidade procurada:\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_a=&#92;frac{1}{120}=&#92;frac{1}{12}\r\n&#92;]', '', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(38, 1685568825, 1685562191, 1685568825, 'b', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.02.b', 'Qual a probabilidade de que o maior n&uacute;mero de emblema seja 5?', '1', 22, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '\r\n  5 n&uacute;meros (1,2,3,4,5) s&atilde;o $&#92;leq$ 5.\r\nCont&eacute;m somente n&uacute;meros menor do que 5:\r\n&#92;[\r\n    &#92;begin{pmatrix}5&#92;&#92;3&#92;end{pmatrix}\r\n    =10\r\n&#92;]\r\nCont&eacute;m somente n&uacute;meros menor do que 4:\r\n&#92;[\r\n    &#92;begin{pmatrix}4&#92;&#92;3&#92;end{pmatrix}\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{4!}{3!(4-3)!}\r\n    =\r\n    4\r\n&#92;]\r\n  \r\nContendo um 5 e os restantes menor: 10-4=6.\r\nProbabilidade procurada:\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_b=&#92;frac{6}{120}=&#92;frac{1}{20}\r\n&#92;]', '$p_b=&#92;frac{1}{20}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(39, 1685564052, 1685563264, 1685564052, 'a', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.03.a', 'Suponha que os tr&ecirc;s digito 1, 2 e 3 sejam escritos em ordem aleat&oacute;ria. Qual a probabilidade de que ao menos um d&iacute;gito ocupe seu lugar pr&oacute;prio?', '1', 23, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '1', 'Podemos posicionar 1, 2 e 3 em 3!=6 maneiras:\r\n   123, 132, 213, 231, 312, 321.\r\n   4 desses tem um d&iacute;gito no lugar certo\r\n   &#92;[\r\n      p_a=&#92;frac{4}{6}=&#92;frac{2}{3}\r\n   &#92;]', '$p_a=&#92;frac{4}{6}=frac{2}{3}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(40, 1685564620, 1685563452, 1685564620, 'b', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.03.b', 'O mesmo que em (a) com os d&iacute;gitos 1, 2, 3 e 4.', '1', 23, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '1', '1 a 4 em 4!=24 maneiras:\r\n \r\n&#92;[\r\n &#92;begin{array}{ccccc|}\r\n 1&amp;2&amp;3&amp;4&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 1&amp;2&amp;4&amp;3&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 1&amp;3&amp;2&amp;4&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 1&amp;3&amp;4&amp;3&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 1&amp;4&amp;2&amp;3&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 1&amp;4&amp;3&amp;2&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n &#92;hline\r\n &amp;&amp;&amp;&amp;6\r\n &#92;end{array}\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\n&#92;[ \r\n &#92;begin{array}{ccccc|}\r\n 2&amp;1&amp;3&amp;4&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 2&amp;1&amp;4&amp;3&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 2&amp;3&amp;1&amp;4&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 2&amp;3&amp;4&amp;1&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 2&amp;4&amp;3&amp;1&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 2&amp;4&amp;1&amp;3&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n &#92;hline\r\n &amp;&amp;&amp;&amp;2\r\n &#92;end{array}\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\n&#92;[ \r\n &#92;begin{array}{ccccc|}\r\n 3&amp;2&amp;1&amp;4&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 3&amp;2&amp;4&amp;1&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 3&amp;1&amp;2&amp;4&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 3&amp;1&amp;4&amp;2&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 3&amp;4&amp;2&amp;1&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 3&amp;4&amp;1&amp;2&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n &#92;hline\r\n &amp;&amp;&amp;&amp;3\r\n &#92;end{array}\r\n&#92;]\r\n \r\n&#92;[\r\n &#92;begin{array}{ccccc|c}\r\n 4&amp;2&amp;3&amp;1&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 4&amp;2&amp;1&amp;3&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n 4&amp;3&amp;2&amp;1&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 4&amp;3&amp;1&amp;2&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 4&amp;1&amp;2&amp;3&amp;$&#92;frown$&#92;&#92;\r\n 4&amp;1&amp;3&amp;2&amp;$&#92;smile$&#92;&#92;\r\n &#92;hline\r\n &amp;&amp;&amp;&amp;3&amp;15\r\n &#92;end{array}\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\n &#92;[\r\n p_b=&#92;frac{15}{24}=&#92;frac{5}{8}\r\n &#92;]', '$p_b=&#92;frac{15}{24}=&#92;frac{5}{8}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(41, 1685563937, 1685563566, 1685563937, 'c', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.03.c', 'O mesmo que em (a) com os d&iacute;gitos 1, 2, 3,... $n$.\r\n \r\n &#92;emph{Sugest&atilde;o}: Empregue (1.7).', '1', 23, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '1', 'Caso $n$. Sugest&atilde;o (1.7):\r\n&#92;[\r\n    P(A_1 &#92;cup A_2 &#92;cup ...&#92;cup A_k)\r\n    =   \r\n    &#92;sum_{i=1}^k P(A_i)\r\n    -\r\n    &#92;sum_{i&lt;j=2}^k P(A_i &#92;cap A_j)\r\n    +\r\n    &#92;sum_{i&lt;j&lt;r=3}^k P(A_i &#92;cap A_j &#92;cap A_r)\r\n    -...+\r\n    (-1)^{k-1}   P(A_i &#92;cap A_j &#92;cap ... &#92;cap  A_k)\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\n$A_i$: D&iacute;gito $i$ no lugar certo. A probablidade do $A_i$\r\n&#92;emph{n&atilde;o} depende do $i$::\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_1=P(A_i)=\r\n       &#92;frac{(n-1)!}{n!}=&#92;frac{1}{n}\r\n&#92;]\r\nSe \r\n$n &#92;geq 2$, $A_{i,j}=A_i &#92;cap A_j$,\r\n$i &#92;neq j$.\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_2=P(A_{i,j})\r\n    =\r\n       &#92;frac{(n-2)!}{n!}=&#92;frac{1}{n(n-1)}\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\nSe \r\n$n &#92;geq 3$, $A_{i,j,r}=A_i &#92;cap A_j &#92;cap A_r$\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_3=P(A_{i,j,r})\r\n    =\r\n       &#92;frac{(n-3)!}{n!}=&#92;frac{1}{n(n-1)(n-2)}\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\nSe  \r\n$n &#92;geq 4$ $A_{i,j,r,s}=A_i &#92;cap A_j &#92;cap A_r &#92;cap A_s$\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_4=P(A_{i,j,r,s})\r\n    =\r\n       &#92;frac{(n-4)!}{n!}=&#92;frac{1}{n(n-1)(n-2)(n-3)}\r\n&#92;]\r\n\r\nEm geral, para $k&lt;n$:\r\n&#92;[\r\n    p_k\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{(n-k)!}{n!}\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{1}{n (n-1) &#92;cdot (n-k+1)},\r\n&#92;]\r\nquanto\r\n&#92;[ \r\n    p_n\r\n    =\r\n    p_{n-1}\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;frac{1}{n!}\r\n&#92;]', '', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(42, 1685563967, 1685563819, 1685563967, 'd', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.03.d', 'Examine a resposta de (c) para $n$ grande.', '1', 23, 1, '1', '1', '1', '1', '1', 'Deixando $n &#92;rightarrow +&#92;infty$:\r\n&#92;[\r\n    &#92;lim_{n &#92;rightarrow +&#92;infty} &#92;pi(n)\r\n    =\r\n    &#92;sum_{i=1}^{+&#92;infty}\r\n    &#92;frac{(-1)^{i-1}}{i!}\r\n    =\r\n    1-\r\n    &#92;sum_{i=0}^{+&#92;infty}\r\n    &#92;frac{(-1)^i}{i!}\r\n    =\r\n    1-&#92;frac{1}{e}\r\n    &#92;simeq\r\n    0.632120559\r\n&#92;]', '$1-&#92;frac{1}{e}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(43, 1685569442, 1685565966, 1685569442, '04.a', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.04.a', 'Qual a probabilidade de que ejam encontradas exatamente 90 pe&ccedil;as defeituosas?', '1', 24, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '', '', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(44, 1685569634, 1685566033, 1685569634, '04.b', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.04.b', 'Qual a probabilidade de que ejam encontram ao menos 2 pe&ccedil;as defeituosas?', '1', 24, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '', '', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(45, 1685569948, 1685566535, 1685569948, '02.06.a', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.06.a', 'Ela n&atilde;o tenha defeitos.', '1', 26, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_a=p_1=&#92;frac{5}{8}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{5}{8}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(46, 1685569954, 1685566576, 1685569954, '02.06.b', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.06.b', 'Ela n&atilde;o tenha defeitos graves.', '1', 26, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_b=1-p_2=1-&#92;frac{1}{8}=&#92;frac{7}{8}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{7}{8$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(47, 1685569963, 1685566601, 1685569963, '02.06.c', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.06.c', 'Ela ou seja perfeita ou tenha defeitos.', '1', 26, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_c=p_1+p_3=&#92;frac{5}{8}+&#92;frac{1}{8}=&#92;frac{3}{4}\r\n &#92;]', '', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(48, 1685570238, 1685567052, 1685570238, '07.a', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.07.a', 'Ambos sejam perfeitos.', '1', 27, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_a=\r\n     &#92;frac{10}{16} &#92;cdot &#92;frac{9}{15}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{5}{8} &#92;cdot&#92;frac{3}{5}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{3}{8}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{3}{8}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(49, 1685570244, 1685567261, 1685570244, '07.b', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.07.b', 'Ambos tenham defeitos graves.', '1', 27, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_b=\r\n     &#92;frac{2}{16} &#92;cdot &#92;frac{1}{15}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{1}{120}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{1}{120}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(50, 1685570250, 1685567315, 1685570251, '07.c', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.07.c', 'Ao menus um seja perfeito.', '1', 27, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', 'Um (de 2) perfeito\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p=\r\n     &#92;frac{10}{16}&#92;cdot &#92;frac{6}{15}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{60}{15 &#92;cdot 16}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{2}{8}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{1}{4}\r\n &#92;]\r\n Os dois perfeitos em (a). Soma:\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_c=\r\n     &#92;frac{1}{4}+&#92;frac{3}{8}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{5}{8}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{5}{8}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52, 1685570256, 1685567442, 1685570256, '07.d', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.07.d', 'No m&aacute;ximo um seja perfeito.', '1', 27, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', 'Nenhum perfeito:\r\n &#92;[     \r\n     p=\r\n     &#92;frac{6}{16}&#92;cdot &#92;frac{5}{15}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{30}{15 &#92;cdot 16}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{1}{8}\r\n &#92;]\r\n Somando com a primeira probabilidade de item (c):\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_d=&#92;frac{1}{8}+&#92;frac{1}{4}=&#92;frac{3}{8}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{3}{8}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53, 1685570262, 1685567464, 1685570262, '07.e', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.07.e', 'Exatamente um seja perfeito.', '1', 27, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', 'Encontrado no item anterior:\r\n &#92;[\r\n     p_e=&#92;frac{1}{4}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{1}{4}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(54, 1685570675, 1685567486, 1685570675, '07.f', 'Exerc&iacute;cio 02.07.f', 'Nenhum deles tenha defeitos graves.', '1', 27, 1, '1', '1', '11', '2', '1', '&#92;[\r\n     p_f=\r\n     &#92;frac{14}{16}&#92;cdot &#92;frac{13}{15}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{182}{240}\r\n     =\r\n     &#92;frac{91}{120}\r\n &#92;]', '$&#92;frac{91}{120}$.', NULL, '2', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
