(120, 1689094379, 1686495295, 1688922384, 'Integra&ccedil;&atilde;o Num&eacute;rica', 'Integra&ccedil;&atilde;o Num&eacute;rica', '<H1>Integra&ccedil;&atilde;o Num&eacute;rica</H1>\n\nDado uma fun&ccedil;&atilde;o <I>cont&iacute;nua</I>, [;f;], em um intervalo finito, [; [a=x_0,b=x_1] ;],\nqueremos estimar num&eacute;ricamente o integral:\n\n<CENTER>\n[; &#92;int_{x_0}^{x_1} f(x) dx ;]\n</CENTER>', '2', 98, 1, '1', '', '1', '1', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/5_Integration', '1', '5_Integration', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(121, 1689100683, 1686497568, 1686497568, 'Polin&ocirc;mios', 'Polin&ocirc;mios', 'Polin&ocirc;mio de grau $n$:\n\n&#92;[\n    P(x)=a_n x^n+a_{n-1} x^{n-1}+...+a_1 x+a_0\n&#92;]\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n     Representa&ccedil;&atilde;o: <SPAN CLASS=Code>v=[1.0,2.0,3.0] #3x^2+2x+1</SPAN>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Visualiza&ccedil;&atilde;o:\n@Code ../../Code/Polynomial.py Polynomia_Print\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Adicionar dois  Polin&ocirc;mios\n@Code ../../Code/Polynomial.py Polynomias_Add\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 116, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/2_Polynomials', '1', '2_Polynomials', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(122, 1689100683, 1686497568, 1686497568, 'Polin&ocirc;mios de Taylor', 'Polin&ocirc;mios de Taylor', '<H1>F&oacute;rmula de Taylor em vizinhan&ccedil;a de \n$x_0$\n</H1>\n\n<CENTER>\n$f(x)=f(x_0)+(x-x_0)f&#92;prime(x_0)+&#92;frac{(x-x_0)^2}{2} f&#92;prime&#92;prime(x_0)+&#92;ldots+&#92;frac{(x-x_0)^n}{n!} f^{(n)}(x_0)+o((x-x_0)^n)$\n</CENTER>\n\nCom:\n\n<CENTER>\n$a_n=&#92;frac{f^{(n)}(x_0)}{n!}$\n</CENTER>\n\nEscrevemos:\n\n<CENTER>\n$f(x)=&#92;sum_{i=0}^n a_n (x-x_0)^n+o((x-x_0)^n)$\n</CENTER>\n\n<BR>\n\nEm uma vizinhan&ccedil;a de \n$x_0=0:$\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n$      e^x=1+x+&#92;frac{1}{2}x^ 2+...+&#92;frac{1}{n!} x^n+o(x^n)$\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$      &#92;cos{x}=1-&#92;frac{1}{2}x^2+...+&#92;frac{(-1)^n }{2n!} x^{2n}+o(x^{2n+1})$\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$      &#92;sin{x}=x-&#92;frac{1}{3!}x^3+...+&#92;frac{ (-1)^n  }{(2n+1)!} x^{2n+1}+o(x^{2n+2})$\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$      &#92;cosh{x}=1+&#92;frac{1}{2}x^2+...+&#92;frac{ 1}{2n!} x^{2n}+o(x^{2n+1})$\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$      &#92;sinh{x}=x+&#92;frac{1}{3!}x^3+...+&#92;frac{1  }{(2n+1)!} x^{2n+1}+o(x^{2n+2})$\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$      &#92;frac{1}{1-x}=1+x+&#92;ldots+x^n+o(x^n)$\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 116, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/3_Taylor', '1', '3_Taylor', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(123, 1689100683, 1686497568, 1686497568, 'Deriva&ccedil;&atilde;o', 'Derivadas Num&eacute;ricas', '<H1>Estimando a Derivada Numericamente</H1>\n\n<UL>\n   <LI>Derivada\n$f &#92;in C^n:$\n      <CENTER>\n$f&#92;prime(t)=&#92;lim_{&#92;varepsilon &#92;rightarrow 0} &#92;frac{f(t+&#92;varepsilon)-f(t) }{ &#92;varepsilon }$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Aproxima&ccedil;&atilde;o pela Defini&ccedil;&atilde;o:\n      <CENTER>\n$f&#92;prime(t)=&#92;frac{f(t+&#92;varepsilon)-f(t) }{ &#92;varepsilon }$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>C&oacute;digo:\n@Code ../../Code/Derivatives.py d_f_1\n@Exec ../../Code/Derivatives.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Duas chamadas da fun&ccedil;&atilde;o</LI>\n</UL>', '2', 116, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/1_Derivatives', '1', '1_Derivatives', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(124, 1689100683, 1686497569, 1686497569, 'Zeros', 'Zeros de Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es', '<H2>Zeros de Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es</H2>\n\nSe:\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n      $f: [a,b] &#92;rightarrow &#92;mathbb{R}$\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n      $f &#92;in C^0([a,b])$\n      (cont&iacute;nua)\n   </LI>\n</OL>\n\nEnt&atilde;o:\n\n&#92;[\n   f(a) f(b)<0 &#92;quad &#92;Rightarrow &#92;quad &#92;exists x &#92;in [a,b]: f(x)=0\n&#92;]', '2', 116, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros', '1', '0_Zeros', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(125, 1689100684, 1686497569, 1686497569, 'Lagrange', 'Interpola&ccedil;&atilde;o de Lagrange', '<H1>Interpola&ccedil;&atilde;o de Lagrange</H1>\n\nLagrange introduziu uma outra abordagem. Considere as Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es de Lagrange, \n$i=0,&#92;ldots,n:$\n\n<CENTER>\n$H_i(x)=&#92;frac{(x-x_0) &#92;cdot &#92;ldots &#92;cdot(x-x_{i-1}) &#92;cdot (x-x_{i+1}) &#92;cdot&#92;ldots &#92;cdot (x-x_n)}{(x_i-x_0) &#92;cdot &#92;ldots &#92;cdot(x_i-x_{i-1}) &#92;cdot (x_i-x_{i+1}) &#92;cdot&#92;ldots &#92;cdot (x_i-x_n)}$\n</CENTER>\n\nObserve que fun&ccedil;&otilde;esas, \n$H_i(x),$\n s&atilde;o polin&ocirc;mios de grau \n$n,$\n e:\n<CENTER>\n$   H_i(x_j)=&#92;delta_{ij}=&#92;left&#92;{&#92;begin{array}{ccc}1,&i=j&#92;&#92;0,& i &#92;neq j&#92;&#92;&#92;end{array}&#92;right.$\n</CENTER>\n\nO Polin&ocirc;mio de Interpla&ccedil;&atilde;o de Lagrange :\n\n<CENTER>\n$P_n(x)=y_0 H_0(x)+y_1 H_1(x)+ &#92;ldots+y_n H_n(x),$\n</CENTER>\nsatisfaz as equa&ccedil;&otilde;es:\n\n<CENTER>\n$P_n(x_i)=y_i,&#92;quad i=0,&#92;ldots,n$\n</CENTER>\n\n\n\n<UL>\n   <LI>\n      Para o uso no seguinte, escrevemos o Polin&ecirc;mio Interpolador para \n$n=1$\n ou seja 2 pontos,\n$       (x_0,y_0) $\ne \n$(x_1,y_1):$\n\n      <CENTER>\n$     H_0(x)=&#92;frac{x-x_1}{x_0-x_1}&#92;qquad H_1(x)=&#92;frac{x-x_0}{x_1-x_0} $\n      </CENTER>\n\n      Polin&ocirc;mio Interpolador linear:\n\n      <CENTER>\n$     P_1(x)=-y_0 &#92;frac{x-x_1}{x_1-x_0}+y_1 &#92;frac{x-x_0}{x_1-x_0}= &#92;frac{1}{x_1-x_0}&#92;left&#92;{(y_1-y_0) x+x_1y_0-x_0y_1&#92;right&#92;}$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n</UL>', '2', 117, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/4_Interpolation/2_Lagrange', '1', '2_Lagrange', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(126, 1689100684, 1686497569, 1686497569, 'Sistema Linear', 'Sistema Linear de Vandermonte', '<H1>Sistema Linear</H1>\n\nDe forma matricial:\n\n<CENTER>\n$&#92;underline{&#92;underline{P}}&#92;underline{x}=&#92;underline{y}$\n\n</CENTER>\n\nA matriz, \n$&#92;underline{&#92;underline{P}}$\n &eacute; do tipo Vandermonte:\n$&#92;underline{&#92;underline{P}}=&#92;underline{&#92;underline{V}}( &#92;underline{x} ).$\nSendo os \n$x_i$\ns distintos, \n$&#92;underline{&#92;underline{P}} $\n&eacute;\nregular, assim a equa&ccedil;&atilde;o acima tem solu&ccedil;&atilde;o &uacute;nica.\nNumericamente, obteremos esta solu&ccedil;&atilde;o, usando o algoritmo do Gauss.\nDe fator, podemos escrever:\n\n<CENTER>\n$&#92;underline{x}=&#92;underline{&#92;underline{P}}^{-1} ~ &#92;underline{y}$\n</CENTER>\n\n@Code ../Interpolation.py Interpolation_Gauss', '2', 117, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/4_Interpolation/1_Linear', '1', '1_Linear', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(127, 1689100685, 1686497569, 1686497569, 'Atividades', 'Atividades 8', '<H1>Atividades 8</H1>\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n     Arquivo N01.py: Para \n$n=2,3,...,10,$\n escolher aleat&oacute;riamente \n$n+1$\n pontos: \n$&#92;underline{p}_i,$\n com\n    abscissas distintas.\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Arquivo N02.py:\n     <OL TYPE=a>\n        <LI>Calcular a matriz de Vandermonte das abscissas e seu determinante.</LI>\n        <LI>Calcular o Polin&ocirc;mio Interpolador, \n$P_n(x),$\n usando Elimina&ccedil;&atilde;o de Gauss.</LI>\n        <LI>Calcular e verificar valores e residuos relativos do \n$P_n(x)$\n nas abscissas \n$x_i.$\n</LI>\n     </OL>\n   </LI>\n    <LI>Arquivo N03.py:\n     <OL TYPE=a>\n        <LI>Calcular as Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es de Lagrange, \n$H_i(x),$\n como Polin&ocirc;mios.</LI>\n        <LI>Calcular o Polin&ocirc;mio Interpolador de Lagrange, \n$P_n(x).$\n</LI>\n        <LI>Calcular e verificar valores e residuos relativos do \n$P_n(x)$\n nas abscissas \n$x_i.$\n</LI>\n     </OL>\n   </LI>\n</OL>\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>N01.py:\n@Code N01.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>N02.py:\n@Code N02.py\n@Exec N02.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>N03.py:\n@Code N03.py\n@Exec N03.py\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 117, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/4_Interpolation/9_Activities', '1', '9_Activities', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
