(141, 1689100683, 1686498552, 1686498552, 'Calcular Valor', 'Calcular Valor de Polin&ocirc;mios', '<H1>Calcular Valores de Polin&ocirc;mios:</H1>\n\nIneficiente, \n$&#92;frac{(n+1)(n+2)}{2}$\n multiplica&ccedil;&otilde;es e \n$n$\n adi&ccedil;&otilde;es:\n\n@Code ../../../Code/Polynomial.py Polynomia_Calc_Dumb\n\nMelhor:\n\n$P(x)=a_0+x(a_1+x(...+x(a_{n-1}+x a_n)...))$\n\n@Code ../../../Code/Polynomial.py Polynomia_Calc', '2', 121, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/2_Polynomials/3_Calc', '1', '3_Calc', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(142, 1689100683, 1686498552, 1686498552, 'Adi&ccedil;&atilde;o', 'Adi&ccedil;&atilde;o de Polin&ocirc;mios', '<H1>Adicionar Polin&ocirc;mios:</H1>\n@Code ../../../Code/Polynomial.py Polynomias_Add', '2', 121, 1, '1', '1', '1', '1', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/2_Polynomials/1_Add', '1', '1_Add', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(143, 1689100683, 1686498983, 1686498983, 'Atividades 3:', 'Atividades 3:', '<H1>Atividades 3:</H1>\n\nPolin&ocirc;mio de grau\n$n:$\n\n<CENTER>\n$P(x)=a_n x^n+a_{n-1} x^{n-1}+a_1 x+a_0$\n</CENTER>\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n     No arquivo N01.py, define os polin&ocirc;mios:\n     <OL TYPE=a>\n         <LI>\n$P_1(x)=x-1$\n         </LI>\n         <LI>\n$P_2(x)=x^2-2x-1$\n         </LI>\n         <LI>\n$P_3(x)=x^3+x^2-x-2$\n         </LI>\n         <LI>\n$P_4(x)=x^4+3x^3-2x^2+x-4.0$\n         </LI>\n         <LI>\n$P_5(x)=x^5-2x^4+x^3+2x-4.0$\n         </LI>\n     </OL>\n@Code N01.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n      Calcule os valores em \n$x=-5,-4,...,4,5.$\n Arquivo N02.py.\n@Code N02.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n      Calcule as somas: \n$P_i(x) + P_j(x), &#92;quad i,j &#92;in [1,...,5]$\n e seus valores para \n$x=-5,-4,...,4,5.$\n      <BR>Arquivo N03.py.\n\n@Code N03.py\n@Exec N03.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n      Calcule os produtos:\n$P_i(x) &#92;cdot P_j(x), &#92;quad i,j &#92;in [1,...,5]$\n e seus valores para \n$x=-5,-4,...,4,5.$\n      <BR>Arquivo N04.py.\n   </LI>\n<OL>', '2', 121, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/2_Polynomials/9_Activities', '1', '9_Activities', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(144, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Atividades', 'Atividades 4', '<H1>Atividades 4</H1>\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>Implemente as <SPAN CLASS=Code>def</SPAN>s das fun&ccedil;&otilde;es no item anterior.\n       Implemente tamb&eacute;m suas coeficientes de Taylor, \n$a_n.$\n       Salvar em Arquivo N01.py.\n\n@Code N01.py\n@Exec N01.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n     Para \n$x=0.5$\n      e as fun&ccedil;&otilde;es no item anterior, calcule os valores\n     do polin&ocirc;mio de Taylor de ordem \n$0,1,...,10.$\n     Salvar em Arquivo N02.py.\n\n@Code N02.py\n@Exec N02.py\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 122, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/3_Taylor/9_Activities', '1', '9_Activities', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(145, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Sim&eacute;trica', 'Aproxima&ccedil;&atilde;o Sim&eacute;trica', '<H1>Aproxima&ccedil;&atilde;o Melhor</H1>\n\n<UL>\n   <LI>\n$n=2p+1:$\n      <CENTER>\n$f(t+&#92;varepsilon) -f(t-&#92;varepsilon)&#92;simeq$\n      </CENTER>\n      <CENTER>\n$2&#92;sum_{j=0}^{p} &#92;frac{ &#92;varepsilon^{2j+1} }{(2j+1)!}  f^{(2j+1)} (t)=$\n      </CENTER>\n      <CENTER>\n$2 &#92;varepsilon f&#92;prime(t)+ 2 &#92;frac{&#92;varepsilon^3 }{3!}f^{(3)}(t)+...+2&#92;frac{&#92;varepsilon^{2p+1}}{(2p+1)!}  f^{(2p+1)}(t)$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Isolando\n$f&#92;prime(t):$\n      <CENTER>\n$f&#92;prime(t)$\n      </CENTER>\n      <CENTER>\n$&#92;frac{  f(t+&#92;varepsilon) -f(t-&#92;varepsilon)  }{ 2 &#92;varepsilon }+&#92;frac{&#92;varepsilon^2}{3!}  f^{(3)}(t)+...+&#92;frac{&#92;varepsilon^{2p}}{(2p+1)!}  f^{(2p+1)}(t)=$\n      </CENTER>\n      <CENTER>\n$&#92;frac{  f(t+&#92;varepsilon) -f(t-&#92;varepsilon)  }{ 2 &#92;varepsilon } +o(&#92;varepsilon^2)$\n      </CENTER>\n     <BR>\n@Code ../../../Code/Derivatives.py d_f\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Duas chamadas da fun&ccedil;&atilde;o</LI>\n</UL>', '2', 123, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/1_Derivatives/2_Symmetric', '1', '2_Symmetric', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(146, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Taylor', 'F&oacute;rmula de Taylor', '<H1>F&oacute;rmula de Taylor  com termo de erro de Lagrange, [;&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon);]</H1>\n\n<UL>\n   <LI>F&oacute;rmula de Taylor  com termo de erro de Lagrange, \n$&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon), &#92;varepsilon>0:$\n      <CENTER>\n$      f(t+&#92;varepsilon) =$\n      </CENTER>\n      <CENTER>\n$f(t)+&#92;varepsilon f&#92;prime(t)+&#92;frac{&#92;varepsilon^2}{2}  f&#92;prime &#92;prime(t)+...+&#92;frac{&#92;varepsilon^n}{n!}  f^{(n)}(t)+&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon)=$\n      </CENTER>\n      <CENTER>\n$&#92;sum_{i=0}^n &#92;frac{ &#92;varepsilon^i }{i!}  f^{(i)} (t)+&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon)&#92;sum_{i=0}^n &#92;frac{ &#92;varepsilon^i }{i!}=  f^{(i)} (t)+&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon)$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$      &#92;exists &#92;xi &#92;in [t,t+&#92;varepsilon],$\n tal que:\n\n      <CENTER>\n$|&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon)|&#92;leq&#92;frac{ &#92;varepsilon^{n+1} }{ (n+1)! }| f^{(n+1)}(&#92;xi) |$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Anote:\n\n      <CENTER>\n$&#92;lim_{&#92;varepsilon &#92;rightarrow 0}&#92;frac{  &#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon)  }{ &#92;varepsilon^{n}  }=0$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Escrevemos:\n      <CENTER>\n$o(&#92;varepsilon^{n}):=&#92;mathcal{E}_n(t,&#92;varepsilon)$\n      </CENTER>\n      <BR>\n       <CENTER>\n$f&#92;prime(t)=&#92;frac{ f(t+&#92;varepsilon)-f(t)}{&#92;varepsilon} +o(&#92;varepsilon)$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n</UL>', '2', 123, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/1_Derivatives/1_Taylor', '1', '1_Taylor', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(147, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Atividades 2:', 'Atividades 2:', '<H1>Atividade #2:</H1>\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>Consideramos as fun&ccedil;&otilde;es:\n      <OL TYPE=a>\n        <LI>\n$f_{1}(x)=x^2 e^{-x} $\n</LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{2}(x)=&#92;frac{e^{x}}{x^2}$\n </LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{3}(x)=&#92;log{(1+x)}$\n </LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{4}(x)=&#92;sqrt{1+x}$\n </LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{5}(x)=&#92;sqrt{1+x^2}$\n </LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{6}(x)=cos{x}$\n </LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{7}(x)=x&#92;cos{x}$\n </LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{8}(x)= tan(x)$\n</LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{9}(x)= &#92;sinh{x}$\n</LI>\n        <LI>\n$f_{10}(x)= x^2 &#92;sinh{x}$\n</LI>\n     </OL>\n     Encontre a primeira derivada das fun&ccedil;&otilde;es. \n     Implemente, no arquivo N01.py, as fun&ccedil;&otilde;es acima e suas\n     derivadas.\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Para cada uma das fun&ccedil;&otilde;es na quest&atilde;o anterior, \n       nos valores \n$x &#92;in [1,2,5,10,20]:$\n\n       <OL type=i>\n         <LI>A derivada anal&iacute;tica,</LI>\n         <LI>A derivada num&eacute;rica pela defini&ccedil;&atilde;o (<SPAN CLASS=Code1>d_f_1</SPAN>),</LI>\n         <LI>A derivada num&eacute;rica sim&eacute;trica (<SPAN CLASS=Code1>d_f</SPAN>). </LI>\n       </OL>\n       Para ambas\n       as derivadas numericas, calcule tamb&eacute;m os res&iacute;duos\n       absoluto e relativo, produzindo uma tabela como em baixo.\n       Arquivo N02.py. Qual a a melhor aproxima&ccedil;&atilde;o num&eacute;rica da derivada?\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Qual a depend&ecirc;ncia do \n$&#92;varepsilon?  $\nPara cada uma das fun&ccedil;&otilde;es na quest&atilde;o anterior, \n       nos valores \n$&#92;varepsilon &#92;in [10^{-1},10^{-2},10^{-4},10^{-6},10^{-8},10^{-10}]:$\n\n       <OL type=i>\n         <LI>A derivada anal&iacute;tica,</LI>\n         <LI>A derivada num&eacute;rica sim&eacute;trica (<SPAN CLASS=Code1>d_f</SPAN>). </LI>\n       </OL>\n       Para a\n       derivada numerica, calcule tamb&eacute;m os res&iacute;duos\n       absoluto e relativo, produzindo uma tabela como em baixo. Qual um valor ponderado para [;&#92;varepsilon;]?\n       Arquivo N03.py.\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Adicione as segundas derivadas (<SPAN CLASS=Code1>d2f1</SPAN>, <SPAN CLASS=Code1>d2f2</SPAN>,...) ao arquivo N01.py e repete o item 2\n     calculando as segundas derivadas, <SPAN CLASS=Code1>d2_f_1</SPAN> e <SPAN CLASS=Code1>d2_f</SPAN>. \n     Qual a a melhor aproxima&ccedil;&atilde;o para a segunda derivada?\n    Arquivo N04.py. A f&oacute;rmula da sec&ccedil;&atilde;o anterior se verifique?\n</OL>\n\n<H2>C&oacute;digos:</H2>\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n      N01.py:\n@Code N01.py f1 df1 Name1 f2 df2 Name2 d2f1 d2f2\n      Output N01.py:\n@Exec N01.py\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n      N02.py:\n@Code N02.py\n      Output N02.py:\n@Exec N02.py 16\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n      N03.py:\n@Code N03.py\n      Output N03.py:\n@Exec N03.py\n   </LI>\n  <LI>\n      Derivatives.py:\n@Code Derivatives.py d2_f_1 d2_f\n      N01.py:\n@Code N01.py d2f1 d2f2 d2f3 d2f4 d2f5 d2f6 d2f7 d2f8 d2f9 d2f10\n      N04.py:\n@Code N04.py\n      Output N04.py:\n@Exec N04.py\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 123, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/1_Derivatives/9_Activities', '1', '9_Activities', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(148, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Res&iacute;duos', 'Erros e Res&iacute;duos', '<H1>Erros ou Res&iacute;duos</H1>\n\n<UL>\n   <LI>\n$x$\n estimado, \n$x_e,$\n anal&iacute;tica, \n$x_a;$\n   <LI>Res&iacute;duo Absoluto:\n      <CENTER>\n$r_a=|x_{e}-x_{a}|$\n      </CENTER>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>Res&iacute;duo Relativo, \n$x_{a} &#92;neq 0:$\n      <CENTER>\n$r_r= &#92;left| &#92;frac{ x_{e}-x_{a}    } {  x_{a}     } &#92;right|$\n      </CENTER>\n     <BR>\n@Code ../../../Code/Residual.py\n@Exec ../../../Code/Residual.py\n   </LI>\n</UL>', '2', 123, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/1_Derivatives/3_Erros', '1', '3_Erros', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(149, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, '2a Derivada', '2a Derivada', '<H1>Estimando a Segunda Derivada</H1>\n\n<UL>\n   <LI>Podemos tentar escrever:\n      <CENTER>\n$f&#92;prime &#92;prime(t)=&#92;frac{f&#92;prime(t+&#92;varepsilon)-f&#92;prime(t-&#92;varepsilon)}{2 &#92;varepsilon}=&#92;frac{f(t+2&#92;varepsilon)+f(t-2&#92;varepsilon)}{(2 &#92;varepsilon)^2}$\n      </CENTER>\n     <BR>\n@Code ../../../Code/Derivatives.py d2_f_1 d2_f\n\n     Ser&aacute; que podemos justificar isso numericalmente? A resposta &eacute;, N&Atilde;O, veja Ativadade 2.4\n   </LI>\n</UL>', '2', 123, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/1_Derivatives/4_2Derivative', '1', '4_2Derivative', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(150, 1689100683, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Isolamento', 'Isolamento de Ra&iacute;zes', '<H2>Isolamento de um Zero</H2>\n\nDado $N>1$, define $x_i$, $i=0,1,...,N$, <I>equidistantes</I>:\n\n&#92;[\n   x_i=a+i &#92;frac{b-a}{N}:=a+i &#92;Delta\n&#92;]\n\n<H3>Algoritmo, dado $N_{Max}&gt; 1$:</H3>\n<UL>\n   <LI>N=2;</LI>\n   <LI>while (N &leq; N<SUB>Max</SUB>):</LI>\n   <OL>\n     <LI>for i=0,...,N:\n     <OL type =i>\n       <LI>\n         Calcular\n         $x_i, f(x_i)$\n      </LI>\n       <LI>if\n          $f(x_i)*f(x_{i-1})<0:$\n         <OL type=a>\n            <LI>Done:\n             $a,b=x_i,x_{i-1}$\n            </LI>\n         </OL>\n     </OL>\n     <LI>N=N+1</LI>\n   </OL>\n   <LI>Still here: Fail!</LI>\n</UL>\n\n@Code Isolate.py\n\n@Code Run.py\n\n@Exec Run.py', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/0_Isolamento', '1', '0_Isolamento', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(151, 1689100684, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Bisec&ccedil;&atilde;o', 'Zeros de Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es', '<H2>Bisec&ccedil;&atilde;o</H2>\n\nDado fun&ccedil;&atilde;o, \n$f,$\n cont&iacute;nua no intervalo\n$[a,b],$\n tal que:\n$f(a)*f(b) < 0$\n\n<H3>Algoritmo:</H3>\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>if\n$f(a)*f(b)>0:$\n croak!</LI>\n   <LI>else:\n      <OL TYPE=a>\n        <LI>while\n$          |f(x)|> &#92;varepsilon$\n          e/ou\n$          |b-a| > &#92;varepsilon:$\n            <OL type=i>\n                <LI>\n$                   x=0.5(b+a)$\n                </LI>\n                <LI>if\n$                   f(a)*f(x) < 0:$\n$                   b=x$\n                </LI>\n                <LI>else:\n$                   a=x$\n               </LI>\n           </OL>\n        </LI>\n     </OL>\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/1_Bisection', '1', '1_Bisection', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(152, 1689100684, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Secante', 'M&eacute;todo da Secante', 'O algoritmo Newton-Raphson requer que conhecemos a derivada da fun&ccedil;&atilde;o. Caso esse nao &eacute; dispon&iacute;vel,\npodemos aplicar o M&eacute;todo da Secante, onde substituimos a derivada por:\n\n<CENTER>\n$f&#92;prime(x_k)=&#92;frac{ f(x_k)-f(x_{k-1}) }{ x_k-x_{k-1}}$\n</CENTER>\n\nObserve, que precisamos acesso a <B>2</B> iteratos anteriores, inicializando o algoritmo com\n$x_0$\n e \n$x_1.$', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/5_Secante', '1', '5_Secante', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(153, 1689100684, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Atividades 1.6:', 'Atividades 1.6:', '<H2>Atividade #1.6-01:</H2>\nCrie um arquivo, Functions4.py, implementando as seguintes fun&ccedil;&otilde;es:\n      <OL TYPE=a>\n        <LI>\n           $f_{1}(x)=e^{-x^2}-&#92;cos{x},  &#92;varphi_1(x)=&#92;cos{x}-e^{-x^2}+x,     a=x_0=1.0, b=x_1=2.0$;\n        </LI>\n        <LI>\n           $f_{2}(x)=x^3-x-1,           &#92;varphi_2(x)=&#92;sqrt[3]{x+1},          a=x_0=1.0, b=x_1=2.0$;\n        </LI>\n        <LI>\n           $f_{3}(x)=4 &#92;sin{x}-e^x,     &#92;varphi_3(x)=x-2&#92;sin{x}+0.5e^x,      a=x_0=0, b=x_1=1$;\n        </LI>\n        <LI>\n           $f_4(x)=x &#92;log_{10} x,       &#92;varphi_4(x)= x-1.3(x &#92;log_{10}x-1), a=x_0=2.0, b=x1=3.0$.\n        </LI>\n     </OL>\nCrie um executavel, Run.All.py, executando todos os algoritmos implementados.\n\n@Code Functions4.py\n\n@Code 01.py\n@Exec 01.py', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/99_Activities', '1', '99_Activities', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(154, 1689100684, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Ponto Fixo', 'Zeros de Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es', '<H2>Ponto Fixo</H2>\n\nSuponhe que existe <I>Fun&ccedil;&atilde;o Iterativa</I>,\n$&#92;varphi(x):$\n\n<P ALIGN=center>\n$f(x)=0 &#92;qquad &#92;Leftrightarrow &#92;qquad x=&#92;varphi(x),&#92;qquad x &#92;in I &#92;subset R$\n</BR>\n\n<H3>Teorema</H3>\n\nSe\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n$&#92;xi$\n ra&iacute;z <I>isolada</I>:\n$f(&#92;xi)=0$\n</LI>\n   <LI>\n$&#92;varphi(x) &#92;in C^1(I)$\n</LI>\n   <LI>\n$&#92;left| &#92;varphi&#92;prime(x) &#92;right| <1, &#92;quad x &#92;in I$\n</LI>\n   <LI>\n$x_0 &#92;in I$\n</LI>\n</OL>\n\nEntao a sequ&ecirc;ncia\n$x_{k+1}=&#92;varphi(x_k), &#92;quad k &#92;in N$\nconverge:\n\n<P ALIGN=center>\n\n$&#92;lim_{k &#92;rightarrow &#92;infty} x_k=&#92;xi$\n\nCrit&eacute;rios de Parada:\n\n<OL>\n   <LI>\n$|f(x_k)|<&#92;varepsilon$\n</LI>\n   <LI>\n$|x_{k+1}-x_k|<&#92;varepsilon$\n</LI>\n   <LI>No de itera&ccedil;&otilde;es > 100 (por ex)</LI>\n</OL>', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/3_Fixed_Point', '1', '3_Fixed_Point', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(155, 1689100684, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Newton-Raphson', 'Zeros de Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es', '<H1>Algoritmo do Newton-Raphson</H1>\n\nNa vizinhan&ccedil;a de um ponto\n$x_k &#92;in I,$\nvale o F&oacute;rmula de Taylor:\n\n<CENTER>\n$f(x) &#92;simeq  f(x_k)+(x-x_k) f (x_k)$\n</CENTER>\n\nPondo [;f(x)=0;], quando\n$f(x_k)&#92;neq 0:$\n<CENTER>\n$x=x_k-&#92;frac{f(x_k)}{f(x_k)}$\n</CENTER>\n\nO que leva a fun&ccedil;&atilde;o iterativa:\n\n<CENTER>\n$&#92;varphi(x)=x-&#92;frac{f(x)}{f(x)}$\n</CENTER>\n\nDerivada:\n\n<CENTER>\n$&#92;varphi(x)=&#92;frac{f(x)f(x)}{f(x)^2}$\n</CENTER>\n\nSupondo que em um intervalo, \n$I,$\n suficientementre pequeno e contendo uma ra&iacute;z, \n$&#92;xi,$\ne que \n$f(&#92;xi) &#92;neq 0, $\npodemos fazer\n$|&#92;varphi(x)|< 1.$\nOu seja,\nsobre estas condi&ccedil;&otilde;es, o algoritmo Newton-Raphson converge.', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/4_Newton_Raphson', '1', '4_Newton_Raphson', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(156, 1689100684, 1686498984, 1686498984, 'Posi&ccedil;&atilde;o Falsa', 'Zeros de Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es', '<H2>M&eacute;todo de Posi&ccedil;&atilde;o Falsa</H2>\n\nCombina&ccedil;&atilde;o Convexa (Reta) entre \n$(a,f(a))$\n e \n$(b,f(b)), $\n$&#92;quad 0 &#92;leq t &#92;leq 1$\n:\n\n<P ALIGN=center>\n$l: &#92;quad &#92;left(&#92;begin{array}{c} x(t)&#92;&#92;y(t) &#92;end{array}&#92;right)=$\n$&#92;left(&#92;begin{array}{c} a&#92;&#92;f(a) &#92;end{array}&#92;right) +t$\n$&#92;left(&#92;begin{array}{c} b-a&#92;&#92;f(b)-f(a) &#92;end{array}&#92;right)=$\n<BR>\n$(1-t)&#92;left(&#92;begin{array}{c} a&#92;&#92;f(a) &#92;end{array}&#92;right)+t$\n$&#92;left(&#92;begin{array}{c} b&#92;&#92;f(b) &#92;end{array}&#92;right)$\n</P>\n<OL>\n   <LI>\nIntersec&ccedil;&atilde;o entre \n$l$\n e o eixo \n$x$\n,\n$t=t_0$\n: \n         <P ALIGN=center>\n$y(t_0)=0 &#92;quad &#92;Leftrightarrow &#92;quad t_0=-&#92;frac{f(a)}{f(b)-f(a)}  &#92;Rightarrow 1-t_0=&#92;frac{f(b)}{f(b)-f(a)}$\n        </P>\n   </LI>\n   <LI>\n$&#92;Rightarrow &#92;quad x(t_0)=&#92;frac{ af(b)-bf(a) }{ f(b)-f(a) }$\n   </LI>\n</OL>', '2', 124, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2', '2', '', '', '/usr/local/Slides/1_Disciplines/1_CN/1_Functions/0_Zeros/2_False_Position', '1', '2_False_Position', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
