(293, 1689271510, 1689271250, 1689271510, 'Singular Points', 'Singular Points', 'The point corresponding to a certain parameter value, $t=t_0$,\r\nis said to be a singular point, if its scalar velocity cancels: $v(t)=0$.\r\n\r\nA point that is not a singular point, ie. $v(t)&gt;0$, is said to be non-singular or regular.', '', 270, 1, '1', '', '7', '2', '1', '', '', '', '2', '3', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
